                            <comment id="84348" author="cbeams" created="Sat, 20 Oct 2012 20:47:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-framework/pull/169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-framework/pull/169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="90607" author="david_syer" created="Wed, 5 Jun 2013 00:23:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;N.B. I have developed the code quite a bit since the PR. It has another home right now, but if anyone wants it here, please shout.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102127" author="snicoll" created="Fri, 18 Apr 2014 05:31:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As we discussed we have a nice support for this in Boot and could consider moving that in the core.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103075" author="john.bryson@resonateinsights.com" created="Wed, 7 May 2014 14:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A few spring modules support YAML, however, Spring Core doesn&#8217;t which makes it really hard to define rich application configuration files. Getting this in would really help us out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103087" author="snicoll" created="Thu, 8 May 2014 03:09:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Spring boot has indeed an excellent support to parse yaml files as properties or map. This support has been migrated to the Spring framework &lt;tt&gt;org.springframework.beans.factory.config.YamlPropertiesFactoryBean&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;org.springframework.beans.factory.config.YamlMapFactoryBean&lt;/tt&gt; respectively.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
